Class CubicInputFunction

java.lang.Object
  edu.bsu.julia.input.InputFunction
      edu.bsu.julia.input.CubicInputFunction

public class CubicInputFunction
extends InputFunction

Description

CubicInputFunction is a subclass of InputFunction representing a function of the form: a*z^3 + b, where a and b are coefficients and all three are complex numbers.

Constructor Summary

evaluateBackwardsRandom

public ComplexNumber evaluateBackwardsRandom(ComplexNumber seed)
Description copied from class: InputFunction
Given a starting value, evaluates the inverse of the function composed with itself m times, and returns a single value. If the function would naturally return more than one value, the method will randomly choose one to return. This method must be overridden by subclasses.
